
Java Script
"""""""""""

JavaScript is one of the 3 languages all web developers must learn:

         HTML to define the content of web pages

         CSS to specify the layout of web pages

         JavaScript to program the behavior of web pages

The <script> Tag
In HTML, JavaScript code is inserted between <script> and </script> tags.


1) Data Types

    Primitive / Value Type & Refference Type
    A const variable cannot be reassigned


    1.1) Primitive Datatypes
                 Number,String,Boolean,Undefine,Null

                 examples:
                            let name='Adarsh';          // String literals
                            let age=27;                 //Number literals      
                            let isapproved=false;       //Boolean literals
                            let firstName=undefined;    //Undefine literals
                            let selectColor=null;       //Null literals
                            
                BigInt:
                            All JavaScript numbers are stored in a a 64-bit floating-point format.
                            JavaScript BigInt is a new datatype (ES2020) that can be used to store integer values that are too big to be represented 
                            by a normal JavaScript Number.

                example:
                            let x = BigInt("123456789012345678901234567890");
   
                The typeof Operator
                                You can use the JavaScript typeof operator to find the type of a JavaScript variable.
                                The typeof operator returns the type of a variable or an expression:
                                
                                Example
                                typeof ""             // Returns "string"
                                typeof "John"         // Returns "string"
                                typeof "John Doe"     // Returns "string"
    
    1.2) Reference Type
                Objects,Arrays,Functions

                1.1) JavaScript Objects
                        
                        

                    example:
                                let person = {
                                        name="adarsh";
                                        age=27;
                                };

                                console.log(person);

                                // dot nottation

                                person.name="arun";
                                console.log(person.log);

                                //bracket nottation

                                person[name]='arun';

                1.2) Arrays

                    example:
                                let selectColors=['red','blue'];
                                selectColor[2]='green';
                                console.log(slectColor);
                                console.log(selectColor.length);

                1.3 Functions
                                Functions are the building blocks in java script

                                example 1:

                                function great(name, lastName){
                                    console.log('Hello'+ name +' '+ lasName);
                                }

                                great(Arun, Lal);
                                great(Depak, Kumar);

                                example 2:

                                function square(number){
                                    return number*number;
                                }

                                console.log(square(2));

                